WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.480
[Amit Varma]: Imagine if COVID-19 had hit the world a few centuries before it actually did.

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:14.920
[Amit Varma]: Before we knew what a virus was, or an ACE2 receptor was, or what natural selection was.

00:00:14.920 --> 00:00:19.040
[Amit Varma]: A time when we couldn't treat any disease because we couldn't understand any disease.

00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:22.400
[Amit Varma]: A time when people considered themselves lucky to live till 30.

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:25.320
[Amit Varma]: A time without ventilators or paracetamols.

00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:28.840
[Amit Varma]: As it happens, imagining that isn't all that hard because we've seen that picture.

00:00:28.840 --> 00:00:33.240
[Amit Varma]: The world has been struck by various pandemics in the past, and the accounts are horrific.

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:37.320
[Amit Varma]: Chinmay Tumbe mentioned them in his fine book, Age of Pandemics, which I discussed with him

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:39.000
[Amit Varma]: in an earlier episode.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.480
[Amit Varma]: Writing about the plague in the 6th century, Chinmay wrote,

00:00:41.480 --> 00:00:46.320
[Amit Varma]: The demographic devastation in the Mediterranean world was stark, with records in multiple

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:51.520
[Amit Varma]: languages describing how thousands of people died in a single day, or how, as per one traveler,

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:56.000
[Amit Varma]: corpses were lying in the fields and along the roadside and cattle wandering untended

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.440
[Amit Varma]: into the hills.

00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.880
[Amit Varma]: The historian Procopius described how the bodies came so fast that those digging the

00:01:02.880 --> 00:01:05.720
[Amit Varma]: trenches to bury them could not dig fast enough.

00:01:05.720 --> 00:01:06.720
[Amit Varma]: What to do with the bodies?

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:10.840
[Amit Varma]: They climbed the towers of the fortifications where they were tore of the roofs and just

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:12.400
[Amit Varma]: piled in the bodies from there.

00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:17.120
[Amit Varma]: When plague struck again in the 14th century, in what is known as the infamous Black Death,

00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:20.120
[Amit Varma]: up to 50 million people are estimated to have died.

00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:23.120
[Amit Varma]: That included 35-60% of Europe.

00:01:23.120 --> 00:01:24.120
[Amit Varma]: Imagine that.

00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:25.720
[Amit Varma]: Half the people around you just gone.

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.120
[Amit Varma]: As if it's the infinity wars.

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:31.040
[Amit Varma]: Well, you're listening to this episode in the middle of the second wave in India, and

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:34.840
[Amit Varma]: the world has been fighting COVID-19 for a year and still not won.

00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:36.320
[Amit Varma]: And yet it could have been far worse.

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:40.080
[Amit Varma]: Here's the thing, our politicians have failed us, our bureaucrats have failed us, policy

00:01:40.080 --> 00:01:44.680
[Amit Varma]: makers have failed us, the dysfunctional state stands exposed for what it is.

00:01:44.680 --> 00:01:47.280
[Amit Varma]: And in so many different ways, we have failed each other.

00:01:47.280 --> 00:01:49.480
[Amit Varma]: But science has not failed us this time.

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:52.440
[Amit Varma]: Unlike in pandemics of past times, we know what is happening.

00:01:52.440 --> 00:01:54.520
[Amit Varma]: We know what we do not know about it.

00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:58.840
[Amit Varma]: And we have made miraculous progress in coming up with the vaccines that we have.

00:01:58.840 --> 00:01:59.840
[Amit Varma]: Is it enough?

00:01:59.840 --> 00:02:00.840
[Amit Varma]: Of course not.

00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:05.160
[Amit Varma]: As my guest on today's show says, vaccines aren't enough, you need vaccinations.

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.960
[Amit Varma]: If I may add to that, human knowledge is not enough.

00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:08.960
[Amit Varma]: You need human action.

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:11.920
[Amit Varma]: There is a lot that is wrong with the world today.

00:02:11.920 --> 00:02:14.860
[Amit Varma]: But there is also a lot that can give us hope.

00:02:14.860 --> 00:02:19.320
[Amit Varma]: Science can give us hope.

