00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.240
[Amit Varma]: and wonderful things in wide-eyed wonder.

00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:15.060
[Amit Varma]: Now, this episode is actually like two episodes in one.

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:18.520
[Amit Varma]: In the first half, we speak of Anirban's journey in the state of modern science and

00:03:18.520 --> 00:03:20.880
[Amit Varma]: academics and science writing and so on.

00:03:20.880 --> 00:03:25.120
[Amit Varma]: In the second half, we speak about COVID-19 itself, what the virus is, what it does, and

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:27.920
[Amit Varma]: the different ways in which science is fighting it.

00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:30.960
[Amit Varma]: I love both halves of this conversation and I hope you do as well.

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:34.920
[Amit Varma]: A quick note before we start, the day after I recorded this conversation, my father died

00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:35.920
[Amit Varma]: of COVID-19.

00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:39.760
[Amit Varma]: He'd been admitted to hospital for other issues a couple of weeks before that and was

00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:41.320
[Amit Varma]: fading in different ways.

00:03:41.320 --> 00:03:43.320
[Amit Varma]: He couldn't recognize me when I last met him.

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:47.000
[Amit Varma]: He picked up COVID at the hospital and spent a few days in a COVID ICU.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:50.520
[Amit Varma]: We weren't allowed to meet him, obviously, but we were allowed one video call a day.

00:03:50.520 --> 00:03:54.960
[Amit Varma]: In those calls, he was unable to speak and we don't even know if he was in his senses.

00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:58.960
[Amit Varma]: And if he wasn't, that could have been a blessing because he was clearly in a lot of suffering.

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:01.040
[Amit Varma]: To be honest, I haven't processed this yet.

00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:04.240
[Amit Varma]: It leads to bigger questions that no one can have an answer for.

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:09.240
[Amit Varma]: As Wittgenstein said, quote, what we cannot speak about, we must pass over in silence.

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:10.240
[Amit Varma]: Stop quote.

